       Be aware that if you change hostname, other  software  may
       break  unexpectedly; so, it is good practice not to change
       hostname once it is set.  For example, networking software
       and  application  packages  may  save the hostname of your
       system at the time the package is  installed.   Therefore,
       each  time you change the hostname, you need to locate all
       the files where it has been saved and change its value.

       You will also need to notify the administrators  of  other
       machines on the network of your machine's new host name.

